## Command Prompt (CMD)

### What is Command Prompt?
**Command Prompt (CMD)** is a text-based tool in Windows that allows
users to type commands to perform tasks on the computer.

### How to Open CMD
- Press **Windows + R**, type **cmd**, press Enter
- Or search **"Command Prompt"** in the Start Menu

### Basic CMD Commands
| Command | What it Does |
|---------|-------------|
| `ipconfig` | Shows your IP address and network info |
| `ping google.com` | Tests internet connection |
| `cls` | Clears the screen |
| `dir` | Lists files in current folder |
| `cd foldername` | Opens a folder |
| `cd ..` | Goes back one folder |
| `mkdir foldername` | Creates a new folder |
| `del filename` | Deletes a file |
| `shutdown /s` | Shuts down the computer |
| `shutdown /r` | Restarts the computer |
| `tasklist` | Shows all running programs |
| `taskkill /IM name` | Stops a running program |
| `sfc /scannow` | Scans and repairs system files |

