## Windows Troubleshooting

### What is Troubleshooting?
Troubleshooting is the process of identifying and fixing problems
on a computer or system.

### Common Problems and Solutions

| Problem | Solution |
|---------|----------|
| Computer is slow | Restart, close unused apps, check Task Manager |
| No internet connection | Check Wi-Fi, restart router, run network troubleshooter |
| App not responding | Open Task Manager → End Task |
| Blue Screen of Death (BSOD) | Restart PC, update drivers, run `sfc /scannow` |
| Computer won't turn on | Check power cable, hold power button 10 seconds |
| Sound not working | Check volume, update audio drivers |
| Windows update failing | Restart PC, check storage space, run Windows Update troubleshooter |
| Virus or malware | Run Windows Defender scan, remove suspicious programs |

### How to Open Troubleshooter in Windows
- Go to **Settings → System → Troubleshoot**
- Select the problem type and follow the steps

### Useful Troubleshooting CMD Commands
| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `sfc /scannow` | Repairs corrupted system files |
| `chkdsk` | Checks hard drive for errors |
| `netsh winsock reset` | Fixes internet connection issues |
| `ipconfig /flushdns` | Clears DNS cache |
| `bootrec /fixmbr` | Fixes boot problems |

